The &quot;virtual state machine&quot; is not really that mathematical. It is
just an =
abstract model of the &quot;a network of Web pages&quot;. So a state
transition of th=
e state machine is always in such a form as the
following
|----------------=
-----|       &quot;click&quot; on a link to the New Page
          |-----------------=
----|
| Current Page |
----------------------------------------------------=
----------------&gt;
|    New  Page |
|---------------------|
                =
        |---------------------|

When a network of web pages is modeled as =
a state machine, the states
in the machine are the &quot;pages&quot; that an agent/br=
owser/application
loads.

When a resource is modeled by using state machine=
 notion, it would be
another story.

